---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy WandaSystems">
  <section class="pt-20 pb-32">
    <div class="container-content">
      <span class="badge mb-4 inline-block">Privacy Policy</span>
      <h1 class="text-heading-1 mb-10 text-text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-prose text-text-secondary">
        <h2 class="text-text-primary">1. Privacy at a glance</h2>
        <p>
          The following information provides a simple overview of what happens to your
          personal data when you visit this website.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-text-primary">2. Hosting</h2>
        <p>
          This website is statically hosted on Cloudflare Pages / Vercel.
          When visiting, technically necessary data (IP address, browser type, timestamp)
          is temporarily stored in server logs.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-text-primary">3. Contact Form</h2>
        <p>
          If you send us inquiries via form or email, your details will be stored
          by us for the purpose of processing the request and in case of follow-up questions.
          We do not share this data without your consent.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-text-primary">4. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions regarding privacy: <a href="mailto:wanda.devops@gmail.com" class="text-brand-gold hover:underline">wanda.devops@gmail.com</a>
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-text-primary">5. Retention and deletion</h2>
        <p>
          We keep personal data only as long as required to process your request, fulfill legal obligations,
          and protect legitimate business interests. If no legal retention duty applies, data is deleted when
          the processing purpose no longer exists.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-text-primary">6. Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          You may request information about stored personal data, correction of inaccurate data, deletion,
          restriction of processing, and data portability where applicable under GDPR.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-text-primary">7. Supervisory authority</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to lodge a complaint with a competent data protection supervisory authority.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
